    explanation: `$R = \\frac{v_0^2\\sin 2\\theta}{g}$ is maximum when $\\sin 2\\theta = 1$, i.e., $2\\theta = 90^\\circ$, giving $\\theta = 45^\\circ$. The maximum range is $R_{\\text{max}} = v_0^2/g$.`
